title: Climate Economics: Practical Applications #1
abstract: This paper investigates recent developments in climate economics and discusses their implications for real-world applications. We present a methodology that combines classical approaches with modern techniques in climate economics to improve robustness and interpretability. Using a real-world dataset, we evaluate the performance of several models and highlight the trade-offs between accuracy and complexity. Our results suggest that domain-specific prior knowledge can significantly enhance model performance in climate economics. Finally, we outline several directions for future research at the intersection of climate economics and data-driven decision making.
author: Julia Chen, Ibrahim Kumar, Samir Smith
